<Defs>
  
<ThingDef ParentName="DrugBase">
<defName>psykwine</defName>
<label>Crömin</label>
<description>A strong and potent mushroom wine containing psychite and alcohol, fermented from the subterranean psykshroom fungus. Crömin glows for unknown reasons, and is customarily stored inside heavy earthenware pots. Opening the vessel, it smells musty, earthy, and stale. But once you get past the smell, the flavour is surprisingly sweet with herbal tones. How crömin came to first be produced is unknown, but it's believed to have originally just been a way to smuggle vast volumes of psychite out of the subterranean fungusariums where the psykshrooms were first engineered and grown. Only some time later did people realize it tasted good too, and the rest is history.

This wine is capable of delivering a potent hit of psychite and alcohol to the imbiber. This contains far more alcohol than beer, and nearly as much psychite as a hit of yayo. Effects scale with drunkenness, and hallucinations manifest at higher levels. It's very easy to accidentally overdose, so be careful!</description>
<descriptionHyperlinks>
      <HediffDef>PsykwineHigh</HediffDef>
      <ThingDef>Plant_Psykshroom</ThingDef>
      <ThingDef>RawPsykcaps</ThingDef>
</descriptionHyperlinks>
